Kenya Airways was forced to cancel a flight on Wednesday&nbsp; after a passenger died at the JKIA in Nairobi.The passenger, 65, died in a plane that was to depart for&nbsp;Mombasa. The man and his family had boarded flight KQ 606 that was to leave at 1.40pm.Passengers said he appeared unwell upon boarding and had to be assisted by staff and ground crew.&nbsp;He died at about 1.30pm. Police were called on the scene and t he body moved&nbsp; from the plane. Passengers wait at the Tranist Lounge at the JKIA following the death of a passenger in a Kenya Airways plane, February 8, 2017. /COURTESYMore to follow